pullRequest.body:
Extend the results in `Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/BilinearForm/TensorProduct.lean` from Bilinear Forms to Bilinear Maps

Similarly for `LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/TensorProduct`.

I had originally intended to extend much more, but was blocked by not being able to extend `LinearMap.IsSymm` from forms to maps.

The existing `BilinMap` names were actually specific to bilinear forms; these have been renamed to make room for the generalizations.

Moves:
- `LinearMap.BilinMap.tensorDistrib` â†’ `LinearMap.BilinForm.tensorDistrib`
- `LinearMap.BilinMap.tensorDistrib_tmul` â†’ `LinearMap.BilinForm.tensorDistrib_tmul`
- `LinearMap.BilinMap.tmul` â†’ `LinearMap.BilinForm.tmul`
- `LinearMap.BilinMap.baseChange` â†’ `LinearMap.BilinForm.baseChange`
- `LinearMap.BilinMap.baseChange_tmul` â†’ `LinearMap.BilinForm.baseChange_tmul`

---

Looks good modulo minor comments
Can you fill out the "moves" section of the PR template to indicate that `BilinMap.tmul` and friends have moved to `BilinForm.tmul`?

This looks quite similar to [LinearEquiv.congrRight](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Equiv/Basic.html#LinearEquiv.congrRight); I think we can use that to implement this?

Thanks. Done. In a similar vein, we can also implement `LinearMap.BilinForm.congr` as:
```
def congr (e : M â‰ƒâ‚—[R] M') : BilinForm R M â‰ƒâ‚—[R] BilinForm R M' :=
  LinearEquiv.congrRight (LinearEquiv.congrLeft _ _ e) â‰ªâ‰«â‚— LinearEquiv.congrLeft _ _ e
```
I've pushed a separate commit with this, but perhaps there are reasons why it was previously done directly? (Performance?)

```suggestion
/-- When `Nâ‚` and `Nâ‚‚` are equivalent, quadratic maps on `M` into `Nâ‚` are equivalent to quadratic
```
What's this?
Must be an artifact. Removed now, thanks.

Could you split this and the corresponding `BilinForm.congrâ‚‚` to their own PR?

It would be good to have the
```lean
@[simp]
theorem congr_refl : congr (.refl R N) = .refl R (QuadraticMap R M N) := rfl

theorem congr_symm (e : N â‰ƒâ‚—[R] P) : congr e.symm = (congr e (M := M)).symm := rfl
```
lemmas for this definition as well, like we do for `BilinForm`.

I also wonder if `LinearEquiv.congrQuadraticMap` would be a better name to match `LinearMap.compQuadraticMap`.

```suggestion
    (BilinMap A Mâ‚ Nâ‚ âŠ—[R] BilinMap R Mâ‚‚ Nâ‚‚) â†’â‚—[A] BilinMap A (Mâ‚ âŠ—[R] Mâ‚‚) (Nâ‚ âŠ—[R] Nâ‚‚) :=
```
Instead of priming this one, let's rename the other one to `BilinForm.tensorDistrib`
Done.
Is this still true? Does "should" here just mean "could be golfed to", or also "has a better defeq as"?
Yes. I meant "should" mathematically as it's then defined as a special case of the `QuadraticMap` version.

@eric-wieser I've pushed a solution, but it's not very pretty as it involves keeping the old definition of `QuadraticForm.tensorDistrib` around as well. Perhaps I should restore the definition I had before and then just add a result to show that it is equal to `(AlgebraTensorModule.rid R A A).congrQuadraticMap.toLinearMap âˆ˜â‚— QuadraticMap.tensorDistrib R A`?

```suggestion
protected abbrev tmul (Bâ‚ : BilinMap A Mâ‚ Nâ‚) (Bâ‚‚ : BilinMap R Mâ‚‚ Nâ‚‚) :
```
Do these exist just for `helper`? I would hope they can be avoided by repairing the proof below.
I've got rid of these definitions and `helper` - essentially by hiding them inside the proof of `associated_tmul`. If that's not good enough, I can have another go tomorrow.
I suspect the right answer here is to prove the `QuadraticMap` version first.
Sorry, I now realize that is a silly suggestion. I think what you have is ok with a comment explaining the unusual proof.
Done, thanks.
Can you put this inside the proof just before `have e1`? After all, this is a comment about the proof, not the theorem
Done, thanks.

For a proper solution we probably want something like:
```
variable [AddCommMonoid M] [CommSemiring R] [Module R M] [StarRing R] [Star M]

/-- The proposition that a sesquilinear form is conjugate symmetric -/
def LinearMap.IsSymm (B : M â†’â‚›â‚—[starRingEnd R] M â†’â‚—[R] R) : Prop :=
  âˆ€ x y, star (B x y) = B y x
```

But preferably with `[NonUnitalSemiring R]` (or even `[NonUnitalNonAssocSemiringSemiring R]`) instead of `[CommSemiring R]` in order that this would cover Hilbert C*-modules.
I've come up with this: #18406
